use new_nb bash script 
new_nb() {
	echo "# %%" > "$1.py"
	jupytext --set-formats ipynb,py:percent --sync "$1.py"
}
e.g. new_nb decision_tree -> creates .ipynb and .py
jupyter lab (launch jupyter)
cells in .py marked by "# %%" at the start of a cell
after edits made in .py, run:
jupytext --sync notebook.py
reload jupyter

If made edit in browser, use :e! in vim to pull these back into buffer.
